{
  "texts": [
    "Considering the potential difficulty of obtaining high-quality training data in the field of interior design, fine-tuning the diffusion model is a more feasible choice.",
    "There are four common methods for fine-tuning the model.",
    "The first, Textual Inversion 24, 32, 37, does not change the weight of the original diffusion model but embeds new knowledge into the original model by providing the most suitable embedding vector for the new training data.",
    "This model can be trained quickly but produces mediocre results.",
    "The second method, Hypernetwork 38, affects the image-generation results by adding additional networks in the middle layers of the original diffusion model."
  ]
}